\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Changes in StrUtils
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 -------------------
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The StrUtils unit contains three sets of changes, all
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 relating to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 multi-byte character set (MBCS) support.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2    * Pre\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 viously, LeftStr, RightStr, and MidStr each
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      took and returned AnsiString values, and did not
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      support MBCS strings. Each of these functions has
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      been replaced by a pair of overloaded functions,
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      one that takes and returns AnsiString, and o\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ne
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      that takes and returns WideString. The new
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      functions correctly handle MBCS strings. This
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      change breaks code that uses these functions to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      store and retrieve byte values in AnsiStrings.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      Such code should use the new byte-level func\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 tions
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      described below.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2    * New functions LeftBStr, RightBStr, and MidBStr
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      provide the byte-level manipulation previously
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      provided by LeftStr, RightStr, and MidStr.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2    * New functions AnsiLeftStr, AnsiRightStr, and
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      AnsiMidStr are the same as the new AnsiStr
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      LeftStr, RightStr, and MidStr functions, except
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      that they are not overloaded with equivalent
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2      WideString functions.
\par 
