\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 dbExpress components and MySQL transactions
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 -------------------------------------------
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 MySQL doesn't support more than one active statement
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 per connection. To perform multiple SQL requests with a
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 single TSQLConnection the dbExpress components clone
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 connection. There is a bug in maintaining state
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 information on the no.of active statements with respect
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 to a TSQLConnection. This might cause serio\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 us failures
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 in transaction as the transaction might be started on
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 one connection and commit or rollback might be
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 happening on another connection.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Workaround:
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Before you start a MySQL transaction make sure
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 TSQLConnection.ActiveStatements is 0. If it's not\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2  0 then
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 close the TSQLConnection and reopen it and that should
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 clear it. All your transaction activity should then go
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 on a single connection.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 DB2 notes for dbExpress
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 -----------------------
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The provided DB2 driver is certified for DB2 version 7.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The clie\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 nt version and server version must be the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 same. BDE also supports DB2 version 7.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Because of a known DB2 bug, the DB2 client returns only
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 one record at a time when a request for a block fetch
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 is made, even with RowsetSize option > 1.
