\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Timestamp issues
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ----------------
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The dbExpress DB2 driver rounds the TIMESTAMP
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 fractional value and there could be some precision lost
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 depending upon the data retrieved. When you apply back
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 changes the old value will not match the one on the
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 server and ApplyUpdates() wil\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 l fail.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Workaround:
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Make sure DB2 TIMESTAMP is not part of indexed columns
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and set the DataSetProvider Update mode to WhereKey
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 instead of WhereAll.
\par 
