\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Oracle LONG and LONG RAW fields (dbExpress)
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 -------------------------------------------
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 When using Oracle, the size of LONG and LONG RAW fields
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 cannot be determined without fetching the whole field.
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 So if BLOB SIZE is set to -1, LONG and LONG RAW fields
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 are truncated to 64K. Recommendation: Set BLOB SIZE to
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 your best estimate of the blob size.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Configuring driver files  (dbExpress)
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ---------------\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ----------------------
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 The Oracle driver now supports Trim Char, Multiple
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Transaction and OS Authentication. You need to add
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 these settings to your dbxdrivers for new aliases
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 and/or update dbxconnections in order to include these
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 settings for old aliases.
\par 
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Please append the following at the end of dbxdrivers
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 file if you are using a driver file from an earlier
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 version of Delphi:
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     [Multiple Transaction]
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     False=0
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     True=1
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     [Trim Char]
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     False=0
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     True=1
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     [OS Authentication]
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     False=0
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     True=1
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Add the following under the [Oracle] section in
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 dbxdrivers and under your existent Oracle alias.
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     OS Authentication=False
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     Multiple Transaction=False
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2     Trim Char=False
\par 
\par 
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 Oracle OS authentication  (dbExpress)
\par \hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ---------------------------\hich\af2\dbch\af23\loch\f2 ----------
